The oily residue is taken up in ethyl acetate and the solution is washed twice with water, dried over sodium sulfate, and evaporated to dryness. The residue is triturated with petroleum ether, affording 25.1 g of 2-hydroxyphenylsulfonamide with a melting point of 136°-138° C.  We discovered that if the amount of methanol in the mixture is above 200 milliliters and the temperature is less than 14 degrees then the product of the process decreases by 10%
